# game-state-model

The game state model tracks critical Spades gameplay elements through defined data structures and relationships:

## Core State Components
- Player states: Track current player positions (4 total)
- Team assignments: North/South vs East/West partnerships
- Active game phase tracking
- Round progression state
- Current trick state

## Bidding System
- Bid collection per player
- Nil/Blind nil bid tracking
- Team bid aggregation
- Bid validation states

## Trick Management
- Active trick participants
- Lead card tracking
- Played cards sequence
- Trick winner determination state
- Trump (Spades) break status

## Scoring Elements
- Team score accumulation
- Bags (overtricks) counting
- Nil/Blind nil bonus tracking
- Round score calculations
- Running game totals

## State Flow Control
Located in src/lib/store.ts:
- Game phase transitions
- Turn sequencing
- Round lifecycle management
- Score updates

